**Server setup documentation**

1. Create an Amazon EC2 account if not already done.

   1. Navigate to <https://signin.aws.amazon.com/signup?request_type=register>

   2. Follow all on-site prompts to create your account. Note that your account will be required to have 2-factor authentication enabled.

2. In the top-right of the navigation bar, ensure that **Asia Pacific (Singapore)** is selected from the drop-down menu. ![A screenshot of a computer

   AI-generated content may be incorrect.](https://lh7-rt.googleusercontent.com/docsz/AD_4nXdGMmJ3WgCT7a5EPrYp7s3v1KNeO4pvf0U3D2zjmgOTeMVpVGL2nWsMFivoZJHzbAUzLA-1-uUcPo1EkPC_tG9csbpVwFkklGRN8abwtsFY0AtVoQqakRwfee-w6PHnSyoKOyRbuA?key=AZxlHjFMsZPfBY2u5xqugw)

3. Navigate EC2 dashboard, then select the orange **Launch instance** button.![A screenshot of a computer

   AI-generated content may be incorrect.](https://lh7-rt.googleusercontent.com/docsz/AD_4nXdDZiBUrZ1VXdaxpNDJWxp66YpocN_dBYKSu8qyvc-hwEONZwFBpWAizSuTdUfbeb-G9MzSDw_txXDKZuGXXH18x99Jofvscvg1LKDxrbxO1zZG_JofFzHYYPVKOfe_ftjsgrQnxg?key=AZxlHjFMsZPfBY2u5xqugw)

4. In the **Applications and OS Images (Amazon Machine Image)** menu, select **Ubuntu** from the **Quick Start** tab. Leave the **Architecture** as **64-bit (x86).**![A screenshot of a computer

   AI-generated content may be incorrect.](https://lh7-rt.googleusercontent.com/docsz/AD_4nXcQucPtb09mCVQ7V_Jj_rkSwVCOcNSx9UjGZetKcp9QgH58gR9eQOOk1TS0UuzbDWM-2slVgy8UQa-w2swcYbevk6sm4LWYqh6rP73zMGfFLHtjCNYLDuoFV0XVx4ArYoN587juMg?key=AZxlHjFMsZPfBY2u5xqugw)

5. Create a new **Key pair.**

   1. On the **Key pair (login)** panel, select the **Create new key pair** link

![A screenshot of a computer

AI-generated content may be incorrect.](https://lh7-rt.googleusercontent.com/docsz/AD_4nXctOP9DghFAMdeGQZ-g4X-CReJiTpUHcX4DRBxWQug66K2dubvJgXnI6GzZl3BKualESw39AeT9LnSgqH9hND3j9MR2gV0omhuTIAmw1Ei4cIkbmAUgecqX-Avwfh_3dXw6qQn2MA?key=AZxlHjFMsZPfBY2u5xqugw)

2. In the **Create key pair** dialog box, enter a name you wish to use for the keys. Ensure that **RSA** is selected for the **Key pair type** and that the **Private key file format** is **.pem**.![Screens screenshot of a computer

   AI-generated content may be incorrect.](https://lh7-rt.googleusercontent.com/docsz/AD_4nXcnETk5FIist9EwI0CaH2TKZ6onXYq3fM1k3BoluCw2kP3laO4hG4FwSsDrmJQbmNvggjDfSe3uleRg1M6gPlCAzg69tyWJfi8-_8iKcgF854TcEZjoZXLx1vAVbvE7pQYBUffA?key=AZxlHjFMsZPfBY2u5xqugw)

3. After selecting **Create new key pair,** a new .pem file will begin downloading. **IMMEDIATELY BACK THIS UP TO YOUR ONEDRIVE OR OTHER SECURE CLOUD STORAGE ACCOUNT**.

![A white paper with a blue check mark

AI-generated content may be incorrect.](https://lh7-rt.googleusercontent.com/docsz/AD_4nXffdk2EbnRVCuQFtYzINbIHeL_NaanAmxYbKDoZ-HA7oxkYc0bmX_6CQn-DlHhi-ft4EyTrXK50nFSz4OGcAsZRhpI-4LPbwIOP3cfM5xtexylN_-v4thRSxUNjihxwElZMjrQi3A?key=AZxlHjFMsZPfBY2u5xqugw)

6. Change to static IP

